io.github.utk003.util.data.collection.bijection

Interface Bijection<A,B>

  • Type Parameters:
    A - The type of objects in the first set of this bijection
    B - The type of objects in the second set of this bijection
    All Superinterfaces:
    Collection<Bijection.Pairing<A,B>>, Iterable<Bijection.Pairing<A,B>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBijection, EnumHashMapBackedBijection, EnumMapBackedBijection, HashMapBackedBijection, MapBackedBijection

    public interface Bijection<A,B>
extends Collection<Bijection.Pairing<A,B>>
    A custom Collection that represents a bijective mapping.

    A Bijection maps two sets of objects in a 1:1 mapping. For more information on bijections, check out https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bijection.

    Since:
    2.0.0
    Version:
    April 23, 2021
    Author:
    Utkarsh Priyam (utk003)
    See Also:

      • containsPairing

        boolean containsPairing(@NotNull
                        A obj1,
                        @NotNull
                        B obj2)
        Returns whether or not this Bijection contains the specified mapping.

        This method is equivalent to running 

        containsPairing(new Pairing<>(obj1, obj2))}
        As a result, only one of these two methods should be explicitly defined. If both are overridden, then both implementations must have exactly the same effect on the internal state of this Bijection.
        Parameters:
        obj1 - The first element of the pairing
        obj2 - The second element of the pairing
        Returns:
        Whether or not this pair is mapped together in the bijection
        See Also:
        containsPairing(Pairing)

      • toPairedArray

        @NotNull
@NotNull Object[][] toPairedArray(boolean makeRowsPairwise)
        Returns this bijection as a 2D array.

        If the argument makeRowsPairwise is true, then the returned 2D array will have dimensions Nx2, where N is the number of mappings in this bijection. Each of the N rows of the array will correspond to a unique mapping of this Bijection.

        If the argument makeRowsPairwise is false, then the returned 2D array will have dimensions 2xN, where N is the number of mappings in this bijection. This will essentially be an array of the two arrays returned by toPairedArray().

        Parameters:
        makeRowsPairwise - Whether to return an Nx2 or 2xN array
        Returns:
        This Bijection as a 2D array
        See Also:
        toPairedArray()

      • addPairing

        boolean addPairing(@NotNull
                   @NotNull Bijection.Pairing<A,B> pairing)
        Adds the specified Pairing to this Bijection, if possible.

        This method is equivalent to running 

        addPairing(pairing.getFirst(), pairing.getSecond())
        As a result, only one of these two methods should be explicitly defined. If both are overridden, then both implementations must have exactly the same effect on the internal state of this Bijection.

        This method returns false regardless of whether the method failed due to the defined pairing existing or due to conflicts with other existing pairings. For a method that throws an exception if the new pairing conflicts, use addPairingOrFail(Pairing), or alternatively use containsPairing(Pairing) to see if the addition failed due to the pairing already existing.

        Parameters:
        pairing - The pairing to add
        Returns:
        Whether or not this Bijection was modified by this method
        See Also:
        addPairing(Object, Object), addPairingOrFail(Pairing)

      • addPairingOrFail

        boolean addPairingOrFail(@NotNull
                         @NotNull Bijection.Pairing<A,B> pairing)
        Adds the specified Pairing to this Bijection, if possible.

        This method completes successfully if and only if the pairing does not conflict with any already existing pairings in the bijection. If this is the case, then this method is identical to addPairing(Pairing). However, if this new pairing does conflict with a pre-existing pairing, then this method throws an IllegalStateException instead.

        Parameters:
        pairing - The pairing to add
        Returns:
        Whether or not this Bijection was modified by this method
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the addition failed due to conflicts with pre-existing pairings
        See Also:
        addPairing(Pairing)

        @NotNull
static <X,Y> @NotNull Bijection<X,Y> makeUnmodifiable(@NotNull
                                                               @NotNull Bijection<X,Y> bijection)
        Returns an unmodifiable Bijection backed by the given Bijection.

        Changes in the original bijection will be reflected in the newly returned copy.
